        <h1 class="leading-10 md:leading-16 mb-[8px] deenullah-regular tracking-tight md:text-6xl">The Division of Juz by Maulana Imran Hosein</h1>
        <hr class="mt-4 md:mt-8 border-1 mb-4">
        <span class="text-[16px] md:text-[20px] font-bold p-2">By Nabeel Aejaz</span><br>
        <span class="text-[16px] md:text-[20px] p-2">December 2, 2025</span>
        <hr class="border-1 mt-4 mb-8">
        <p>Recite the Quran at least once, cover to cover, each month. Try to complete each Juz (portion) on its equivalent lunar date. The Suwar (plural of Surah) have more meaning and significance based on the moon's phases. If a month has 29 days, recite the 30th Juz along with the 1st Juz of next month.</p>
        <p>The daily recitation has numerous benefits. It is a prerequisite for understanding the Quran. It forms a protective barrier against attacks. It also helps you experience time at its natural pace.</p>
        <p>Following is the division of Juz (30 parts) as proposed and recommended by Maulana Imran Hosein in his book <a href="https://imranhosein.org/o/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Text-Final-The-Quran-and-the-Moon-Web.pdf" target="_blank" class="decoration-dashed">‘Quran and the Moon’</a>. The main difference in this division is that the Surah remains intact and does not break into bits and pieces. It is highly recommended to recite Surah Fatiha first before beginning each Surah. As it is the said to be the key to the Quran.</p>
        
      
